517a5040-b47c-517c-a435-202876995370,tg:rubgr:643,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Suicide of Saul. A drawing by Hans Bol, signed and dated 1568, Basel, Küpferstichkabinett (repr. [Heinrich Gerhard] Franz, [Hans Bol als Landschaftszeichner],  Jb.des Kh.Institutes der Univ. Graz [= Jahrbuch des Kunsthistorischen Institutes der Universität Graz], I, 1965, [pp. 19-67], pl. 46, developed from Bruegel. The group of Saul & his shield bearer (?) large in left foreground. On the right the armies with many figures, but background landscape - Weltlandschaft with high mountains follows Patinir & Mathijs Cock tradition rather than Bruegel. Generally in many early Bol drawings,  i.e. before [onleesbaar], trees like in the 'bear' drawings; Ad [Addendum] Months. Drawing by Hans  Bol, signed and dated 1570 in Louvre, Cabinet des dessins, Inv.N° 20908, repr. Franz, Jb.des Kh.Institutes der Univ. Graz, I, 1965, pl. 57. According to Franz representing 2 months: Sept. & October (Look up Lugt in Louvre Catal.) Bol, Seasons, each time with 3 months, and their zodiac signs. Allegorical figure in center. Hermitage, Franz adest plates 101c-101d, text p. 63 designed for engravings by J. Sadeler, date 1580 (Hollstein, III, p. 54, Nos. 228-231, In Winter (pl. 101d) Pisces, Aquarius, Ram, [onleesbaar] of boar at end under Ram.",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Suicide of Saul. A drawing by Hans Bol, signed and dated 1568, Basel, Küpferstichkabinett (repr. [Heinrich Gerhard] Franz, [Hans Bol als Landschaftszeichner],  Jb.des Kh.Institutes der Univ. Graz [= Jahrbuch des Kunsthistorischen Institutes der Universität Graz], I, 1965, [pp. 19-67], pl. 46, developed from Bruegel. The group of Saul & his shield bearer (?) large in left foreground. On the right the armies with many figures, but background landscape - Weltlandschaft with high mountains follows Patinir & Mathijs Cock tradition rather than Bruegel. Generally in many early Bol drawings,  i.e. before [onleesbaar], trees like in the 'bear' drawings; Ad [Addendum] Months. Drawing by Hans  Bol, signed and dated 1570 in Louvre, Cabinet des dessins, Inv.N° 20908, repr. Franz, Jb.des Kh.Institutes der Univ. Graz, I, 1965, pl. 57. According to Franz representing 2 months: Sept. & October (Look up Lugt in Louvre Catal.) Bol, Seasons, each time with 3 months, and their zodiac signs. Allegorical figure in center. Hermitage, Franz adest plates 101c-101d, text p. 63 designed for engravings by J. Sadeler, date 1580 (Hollstein, III, p. 54, Nos. 228-231, In Winter (pl. 101d) Pisces, Aquarius, Ram, [onleesbaar] of boar at end under Ram.</content>
